                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16335262" author="paulk" created="Tue, 23 Jan 2018 01:29:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This functionality isn&apos;t strictly needed. Calling a no-arg constructor with current Groovy versions calls the Map constructor with &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;. However, we should try not to rely on that functionality as much as possible and having this option allows providing a like-for-like replacement of &lt;tt&gt;@Immutable&lt;/tt&gt; with an annotation collector.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
